 Primary Installations
	1. Install Chocolatey.
Install Chocolatey on the Window using the below guide
https://phoenixnap.com/kb/chocolatey-windows
	1. Open  power shell (open as admin) and Use choco to install the required dependencies
	choco install cmake --installargs 'ADD_CMAKE_TO_PATH=System'
	choco install ninja gperf python git dtc-msys2 wget 7zip unzip
	1. Close the window and open a new cmd.exe window as a regular user to continue.
Get Zephyr and install Python dependencies
	1. Create a new virtual environment:
	cd %HOMEPATH%
	1. python -m venv zephyr-v3.2.0\.venv
	2. Activate the virtual environment:
	zephyr-v3.2.0\.venv\Scripts\activate.bat
	1. Install west:
	pip install west
	1. Get the Zephyr source code:
	west init --mr v3.2.0 zephyr-v3.2.0
	cd zephyr-v3.2.0
	cd zephyr
	west update
	1. Export a Zephyr CMake package. This allows CMake to automatically load boilerplate code required for building Zephyr applications.
	west zephyr-export
	1. Zephyr’s scripts\requirements.txt file declares additional Python dependencies. Install them with pip.
	Go to zephyr-v3.2.0\zephyr\scripts\
	pip install -r scripts\requirements.txt
Install Zephyr SDK
	1. Open a cmd.exe window by pressing the Windows key typing “cmd.exe”.
	2. Download the latest Zephyr SDK bundle:
cd %HOMEPATH%
	3. wget  https://github.com/zephyrproject-rtos/sdk-ng/releases/download/v0.15.2/zephyr-sdk-0.15.2_windows-x86_64.zip
 
	1. Extract the Zephyr SDK bundle archive:
	7z x zephyr-sdk-0.15.2_windows-x86_64.zip
	Run the Zephyr SDK bundle setup script:
	cd zephyr-sdk-0.15.2
	setup.cmd
	
	
	Additional steps
	git clone edge rtos
	 -> run setup bat file -> provide 1 as a input
	git clone smart filter  (dev branch) give build cmd
	
